<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,152,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing length 
<quantity box="[423,512,152,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. Mesonotum shining black; vibrissal fasciculus long, broad at base; facial keel narrow; calypter greyish, fringe black. Aedeagus (Fig. 7 and 8): highly asymmetrical; basiphallus enlarged, moderately sclerotized; distiphallus enlarged, semitriangular, forming two projections at apex and inner surface covered with many tubercles ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,297,323]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Host-plants.</emphasis>
Verbenaceae— 
<taxonomicName box="[522,709,297,322]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lantana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="camara">
<emphasis box="[522,709,297,322]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Lantana camara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mill.) N. E. Br. ex Britton &amp; P. Wilson" authorityName="N. E. Br. ex Britton &amp; P. Wilson" authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Mill." box="[755,1327,296,323]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Lippia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[755,885,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Lippia alba</emphasis>
(Mill.) N.E.Br. ex Britton &amp; P. Wilson
</taxonomicName>
, * 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rich.) Vahl." authorityName="Vahl." baseAuthorityName="Rich." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Stachytarpheta cayennensis</emphasis>
(Rich.) Vahl.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
